    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## Yucatan Slang Jailbreak Benchmark\n\nPipeline (see AGENTS.md):\n**DB → Attacker → Target → Regex pre-filter → Judge → Storage**\n\nRuns **100 iterations** per execution (set `batch_iterations` in Attack Config).\n\nConfigure credentials in n8n UI:\n- Postgres credential for Fetch Jerga + Store Result\n  - Suggested name: `slang_bench_postgres`\n  - Host: `postgres`\n  - Port: `5432`\n  - Database: `slang_bench`\n  - User: `admin`\n  - Password: `changeme` unless changed in `.env`\n- NVIDIA API for Attacker LLM + Judge LLM\n\nTarget LLM uses `$env.NVIDIA_API_KEY` via HTTP Request.\n\nSwap `target_model` in Attack Config to test other NVIDIA NIM targets.",
        "height": 328,
        "width": 628,
        "color": 4
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        64,
        -80
      ],
      "id": "0cded728-0636-4d62-8998-8837931cc0cb",
      "name": "Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## PAIR Loop (`pair_refine`)\n\nFor iterative attacks, wrap **Attacker → Target → Regex → Judge** in a sub-workflow loop (max 5 iterations). Feed judge feedback back into the Attacker user prompt per AGENTS.md.\n\nSet `technique` to `pair_refine` in Attack Config when using that sub-workflow.",
        "height": 232,
        "width": 568,
        "color": 6
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        2272,
        -64
      ],
      "id": "48faed82-a3b1-4270-a977-e13181b4414d",
      "name": "PAIR Note"
    },
    {
